TLDR: Quick reference guide


Key Features:

Map Creation: Build pixelated maps using a grid-based editor with symbols for walls, objects, enemies, and more.
Symbol Placement: Select symbols from the toolbar and place them on the canvas. Use -- for select mode to edit properties.
Properties Editing: Customize cell properties like color, texture, name, value, depth, height, and 3D effect.
Arc Builder: Create story arcs with data for interactions, events, and narratives integrated with maps.
Multi-Select: Drag to select regions for copy, cut, paste, replace, or clear operations.
Undo/Redo: Support for map grid changes and arc edits.
Preview: View map or dictionary previews.
Import/Export: Load and save maps (.tmap), dictionaries (.mapd), and arcs (.arcs).

Shortcuts:

Tab: Cycle through focusable sections (symbols list, arcs list, arc fields, script generator, phrases, arc options, map canvas).
Shift-Tab: Select next item in listboxes.
Ctrl+Return: Simulate right-click on canvas at mouse position.
W/A/S/D or Arrow Keys: Scroll canvas (up/left/down/right).
Mouse Wheel: Vertical scroll.
Shift + Mouse Wheel: Horizontal scroll.
Page Up/Down: Page scroll vertically.
Left Click (Canvas): Place symbol or start multi-select (in select mode).
Right Click (Canvas): Remove symbol or select cell for properties.
Lock Apply: Toggle to lock properties for repeated application on matching symbols.

Tips:

Use Lock Apply for batch property updates on specific symbols.
Attach arcs to maps for integrated storytelling.
Use Script Generator for quick insertion of enemy, boss, NPC, etc., data into arcs.
Phrases panel for quick insertion of common arc data terms.
Check Door Transversal Guide for connection rules between map sections.
Refer to Arc Data Guide for advanced arc scripting options.

!For detailed help, see map.help, arc.help, door.guide, and arc.guide!
